  "texts": [
    "Region-based segmentation divides the image into multiple regions based on the similarity of pixels in terms of intensity value, color, and shape.",
    "Two well-known region-based segmentation methods are Region Growing and Region Splitting (Aubry et al., 2014).",
    "The methods to segment the image in both are vice versa, with one growing the region by adding seed pixels of neighboring pixels.",
    "Clustering, another image segmentation approach, groups pixels together based on their similarity in texture, color, or other required features.",
    "K-means (Ell and Sangwine, 2007) and Fuzzy Cmeans (Camargo and Smith, 2009) are famous clustering algorithms for image segmentation and are widely used in various applications."
  ],
